Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.35,0:01:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The attacks by the Gundams\Nsent by the Space Colonies...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.49,0:01:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...reflected the colonies'\Nretaliatory intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ has masked its identity\Nin the Alliance Military...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.23,0:01:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...and the Gundams' missions\Nis to attack them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.67,0:01:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The year is After Colony 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.47,0:01:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ has finally taken\Ncenter stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.14,0:01:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,With an army of elite soldiers\Nat his command...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.71,0:01:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,...Treize Khushrenada has begun to\Nwipe out the Alliance Military.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.32,0:02:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The battle between OZ and the\Nmobile suits sent to Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.12,0:02:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,...causes serious repercussions\Non the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.82,0:02:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've mastered many mobile suits\Nin the past, so what gives?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.66,0:02:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I afraid of?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.30,0:02:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,LONG LIVE, KING ZECHS!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.51,0:02:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My hands are too stained\Nwith blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.88,0:02:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm completely unfit to head\Nthe Peacecraft monarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.30,0:02:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the Tallgeese.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.61,0:02:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see that it's no\Nordinary machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.05,0:03:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that only Zechs\Ncould be its pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.08,0:03:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving Zechs too much special\Ntreatment might not be wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.35,0:03:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're giving a superior\Nsuit to a superior pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.69,0:03:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Any problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.99,0:03:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm concerned that it might\Ngive him an attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.56,0:03:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady, there's no need for\Nyou to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.53,0:03:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus only on the major issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.94,0:03:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.34,0:03:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We've awaited you,\NYour Excellency.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.58,0:03:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to cause you\Nso much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.58,0:03:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.08,0:03:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And Lieutenant Noin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.85,0:03:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I commend you on\Nyour front-line battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.92,0:03:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to thank you personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.55,0:03:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too kind, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should Mr. Treize have\Nto thank his own soldiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And some of them shamelessly\Naccept his praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.56,0:03:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've put Lady Une in charge\Nof our latest plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we get started?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.04,0:03:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:04:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be giving an explanation\Nof our strategy at 1600 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.14,0:04:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then be on your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.38,0:04:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.85,0:04:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Zechs, Lieutenant Noin,\Nyou two shall attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.18,0:04:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.15,0:04:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there was something else\NI wanted to discuss with Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.25,0:04:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll send him soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.52,0:04:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Noin!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.82,0:04:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.93,0:04:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.46,0:04:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe you have a better\Ngrasp of your feelings...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.23,0:04:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,...toward the Alliance by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.83,0:04:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Lightning Baron?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.44,0:04:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Or may I call you\NLightning Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.94,0:04:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Excellency, I was hoping\Nto serve you for a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.24,0:04:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that'd\Nmake me happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.95,0:04:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.11,0:04:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As it is there's only one name\NI could give myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.78,0:04:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Killer of His Own Men.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.79,0:04:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundams?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.82,0:04:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.89,0:04:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, do as you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.76,0:04:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.86,0:04:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, won't you be\Ntaking your mask off?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.63,0:04:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You've carried out\Nyour revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.70,0:05:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need now\Nto hide your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.80,0:05:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I still bring my personal hatred\Nonto the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.97,0:05:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think of this as my\Nmark of distinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.07,0:05:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a very devoted soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.31,0:05:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the reason I can trust\Nyou with anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.55,0:05:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...Milliardo Peacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.62,0:05:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That name...please don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.19,0:05:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to the day\Nyou remove that mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.23,0:05:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The latest plan involves\Ntransporting the Tauruses...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.73,0:05:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...to the Siberian Base to\Ninstall our new mobility system.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.04,0:05:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A new system?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.74,0:05:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I hadn't heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.24,0:05:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Our lack of confidence in\Nthe facilities and security...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.38,0:05:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...at the Lake Victoria base\Nhas led to this transfer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tauruses will be transported\Nacross the Arabian Peninsula...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,...under the heavy guard of\Nour African branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take over the\Ntransfer there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.42,0:05:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So far there haven't been\Nany real threats...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.66,0:06:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,...but we've considered\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.66,0:06:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already announced\Na false transport plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.43,0:06:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't let the enemies\Nhave it their way this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.33,0:06:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundams?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.50,0:06:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundams have attacked\Npractically all of OZ's operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.70,0:06:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This should be another\Nattractive target for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But as long as I'm in charge,\NI'll prevent such interference!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're going to Siberia...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,...they can pass through\NOZ's protected areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.88,0:06:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Gundams\Nwon't be able to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we want them to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I consider annihilating the\NGundams a big part of this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.26,0:06:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Our losses up until now were\Nbecause cowardly soldiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.69,0:06:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...were too slow compiling\Ntheir data.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.46,0:06:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time OZ is serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.10,0:06:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to give an example of\Nhow to eradicate the Gundams.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.80,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It might not come to much use,\Nbut let me provide you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...with some background.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.38,0:06:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. J!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll refer to the unit that\Nfell over the Pacific Ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.59,0:07:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...as Gundam Zero One.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.09,0:07:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Most remarkable is\Nits mobility...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.43,0:07:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...as an aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll lure it to an Aries air\Nzone and shoot it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Without its wings, we can\Novercome it in a long battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.67,0:07:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, the Gundam Zero Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.37,0:07:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Taurus is a problem.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.24,0:07:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It has the ability to learn{\i0}\N{\i1}from accumulated battle data.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wanna trust OZ's control{\i0}\N{\i1}system, but it's possible...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.84,0:07:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...the machine will ignore the{\i0}\N{\i1}pilot's commands and act alone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.55,0:07:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If the command to kill{\i0}\N{\i1}overrides the pilot...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.89,0:07:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...the consequences could{\i0}\N{\i1}be significant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.75,0:07:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Destroy it, otherwise it'll{\i0}\N{\i1}be a menace to mankind.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.49,0:07:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mission accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.86,0:07:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.63,0:07:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come to say good-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.16,0:07:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ's transport plan is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.57,0:07:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be taking two routes;\Nby air and land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.78,0:07:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero, could you take\Nthe air route?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.71,0:08:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll fight them on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.55,0:08:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll lose unless we have\Nour own plan, this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero Two's features allow it to\Nremain unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.59,0:08:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It specializes in close combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.19,0:08:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It is important to make\NZero Three use up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.13,0:08:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...all of its firepower at\Nan early stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.46,0:08:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is true for all of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...but not one mobile suit\Nexcels in organized battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.08,0:08:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no choice but to attack\Nwhile they're transporting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with such basic tactics...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.05,0:08:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...if they can trick us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,...our fighting power will\Nbe dispersed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.42,0:08:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,By air?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.12,0:08:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll take the land!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.99,0:08:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They might come by air.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.52,0:08:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If we hit their land\Ntransport early...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...we can tell everyone\Nwhich one's the decoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.13,0:08:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You think the other Gundams\Nwill come?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.53,0:08:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't win by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.87,0:08:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm positive the\Nothers will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.38,0:09:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm no longer able to fight\Nin my current state.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.02,0:09:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Denounce me, Nataku.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.56,0:09:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero Four is also a close-range\Nbattle type...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...but we believe its battle\Nrange is broader than Zero Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.36,0:09:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid direct combat with Zero Five.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.93,0:09:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Barrage until it's destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.07,0:09:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Be extremely cautious of\Nthe firepower in its left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.77,0:09:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That concludes my briefing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.04,0:09:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather the troops of the\Nrespective bases...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,...along this route to standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.74,0:09:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.42,0:09:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Zechs, I was hoping\Nyou'd take on the task...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.15,0:09:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...of fighting Zero One with the\NTallgeese, one on one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.79,0:09:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.22,0:09:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't expect him\Nto go alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.72,0:09:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll back him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.39,0:09:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But Noin...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.86,0:09:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There are still some Aries\Nleft in the Lake Victoria base.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.63,0:10:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I request orders to lead\Nthe Aries to battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.63,0:10:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm appointing you\Nto the headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.50,0:10:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be assisting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.24,0:10:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Any problems with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.31,0:10:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.61,0:10:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Zechs previously\Nreceived a serious blow...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...at the hands of Zero One.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.38,0:10:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that he has the Tallgeese...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.42,0:10:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,...this would be the perfect\Nopportunity to get his revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.59,0:10:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.09,0:10:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If he loses it all becomes\NZechs' fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.16,0:10:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin, it suits me fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.16,0:10:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping you'd be\Nstationed at the headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.23,0:10:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When we fight we'll need\Nquick, accurate information.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.77,0:10:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll need your support.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.14,0:10:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.24,0:10:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence operations!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.75,0:10:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Relena!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.05,0:10:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.55,0:10:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Relena, something awful's\Nhappened!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero has changed schools,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.82,0:10:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You already knew about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.22,0:10:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We hadn't even become friends\Nwith Heero and Duo yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.19,0:11:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Off to fight again, Heero?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.46,0:11:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm headed for my\Nown battleground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.80,0:11:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile suit troop preparation\Nfor both the flight course...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.90,0:11:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...and the railway course\Nare complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.21,0:11:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the observation satellite\Nfor course irregularities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.91,0:11:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.68,0:11:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.85,0:11:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Colonel Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.21,0:11:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Which carrier route will\Nthey be using?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.38,0:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are extremely important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.52,0:11:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Gundam Zero Four located 9.0 kilometers\Nfrom land route point A.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.39,0:11:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.12,0:11:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Aries No. 4 squadron, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.40,0:11:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There's our target,\NMaster Quatre!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.66,0:12:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No mistaking this security!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.56,0:12:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's this route!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.34,0:12:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.46,0:12:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey, are you okay?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.66,0:12:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm fine.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.73,0:12:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Glad you came.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.13,0:12:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.37,0:12:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But this route's the decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.04,0:12:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.68,0:13:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Radar plane reporting!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.88,0:13:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A high speed carrier's{\i0}\N{\i1}headed our way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.45,0:13:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Release mobile suits{\i0}\N{\i1}for counterattack!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.07,0:13:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Taurus carriers have{\i0}\N{\i1}arrived at its fueling point.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.51,0:13:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Backup Defense Army, attack!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.26,0:13:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Flying object approaching\Nfrom south-east at high speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably Zero One.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll arrive at the supply base\Nin T-minus 300.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.53,0:13:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.36,0:13:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero One has just arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.13,0:13:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's headed for the air route\Nsupply point...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.60,0:13:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...where we're fighting off Zero Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.81,0:14:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.21,0:14:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's headed for the air route.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.14,0:14:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be close, but I'll\Ntake him out midway!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That an Aries?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.47,0:14:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No it's bigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Data checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.18,0:14:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No match to the latest\NOZ weapons?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.85,0:14:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.30,0:15:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Gundam Zero One.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.37,0:15:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no need for beam\Nrifles or cannons between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.68,0:15:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fight for recognition\Nof superiority.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.71,0:15:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that'll suit you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.12,0:15:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You ARE a Gundam pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.87,0:15:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the flight type.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.51,0:15:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a new OZ model?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.92,0:15:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe I've won this battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.52,0:15:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel no fear whatsoever!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.89,0:16:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I can defeat you without taking\NTallgeese to its full limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Prototype Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.70,0:16:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So OZ has completed them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.83,0:16:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be easy,\Nbut I'll destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My mission's to destroy\Nthe Taurus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.57,0:16:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm checking out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.21,0:16:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Half the land route Leo\Ntroops have been defeated...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.05,0:16:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...by Zero Two and Zero Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.62,0:16:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero One is battling the Tallgeese.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.49,0:16:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But Zero Three is headed for\Nthe supply base.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would've guessed\NGundams had this much power?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.62,0:16:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Taurus carriers are on\Nstandby for emergency take off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.96,0:16:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give the "okay".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.06,0:16:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't approve that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.23,0:16:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My strategies never fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.64,0:16:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Get Space Fortress Barge\Non line!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.84,0:16:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A Space Fortress?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.37,0:16:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Colonel Une, positioning{\i0}\N{\i1}is complete.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.74,0:16:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling all Gundam pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.15,0:16:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We're ready to stage an all-out\Nmissile attack on the colonies!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've seized all missile{\i0}\N{\i1}satellites from the Alliance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.85,0:17:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now we truly control the{\i0}\N{\i1}destiny of all colonies!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.83,0:17:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a bluff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.36,0:17:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I demand all pilots to\Nsurrender at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.67,0:17:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and hand over your Gundams!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.37,0:17:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They've targeted the colonies!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.54,0:17:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hand over our Gundams?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.81,0:17:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like OZ's tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.01,0:17:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell of a time for tasteless\Ntactics!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.51,0:17:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys can't fight, can you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.99,0:17:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't fight either!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Noin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.39,0:17:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me Lady Une!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.93,0:17:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundams have stopped,\Nbut they aren't surrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.80,0:17:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Launch a missile!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.16,0:17:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care where!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.87,0:17:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Colonel!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.90,0:17:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Get a grip on yourself!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.57,0:17:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I know exactly what I'm doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.20,0:17:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That isn't what His{\i0}\N{\i1}Excellency wants!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.71,0:17:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm merely fulfilling\NHis Excellency's ideal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.68,0:18:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You clearly don't understand{\i0}\N{\i1}His Excellency!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.42,0:18:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one that doesn't\Nunderstand him, Zechs!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.95,0:18:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.55,0:18:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.05,0:18:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The objective is to eliminate\Nthe rebels.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.39,0:18:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,His Excellency doesn't want\Nbattles that involve civilians.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.00,0:18:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies can be flattened\Nwith the most minute of attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.50,0:18:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're insignificant worlds\Nfor the pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.20,0:18:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the rebels?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.74,0:18:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll sweep them all away\Nwith this single command!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.48,0:18:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Launch missiles!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.71,0:18:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No, don't!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.68,0:18:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What on earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.08,0:18:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.25,0:18:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Attention OZ.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.02,0:18:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I never imagined you people{\i0}\N{\i1}could be so foolish.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.89,0:18:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Space Colonies have{\i0}\N{\i1}no intention of fighting OZ.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.93,0:18:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is MY personal battle{\i0}\N{\i1}I'm staging against you!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.80,0:18:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.30,0:18:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. J...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.90,0:18:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rebel's finally\Nshowing his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.37,0:19:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission is on a regular\Nline from outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission origin is\NColony C-1013.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.24,0:19:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who's been\Nsending orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.88,0:19:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To one of us five Gundams!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.15,0:19:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To you, inhumane moves like{\i0}\N{\i1}colony assaults are justified...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.05,0:19:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...if that's what it takes for{\i0}\N{\i1}you to come out victorious.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.26,0:19:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have no choice but{\i0}\N{\i1}to surrender.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.23,0:19:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.06,0:19:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Your surrender's accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.46,0:19:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon your Gundams\Nimmediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.44,0:19:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilot of a Gundam is\Na little boy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.37,0:19:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I surrender.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.84,0:19:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I will not hand over{\i0}\N{\i1}the Gundams. I repeat.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.08,0:19:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I surrender, but I will not{\i0}\N{\i1}hand over the Gundam.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mission accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.86,0:20:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero One just...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.93,0:20:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...self-detonated...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.46,0:20:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That pilot sacrificed\Nhis life!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.77,0:20:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He self-detonated in\Nexchange for the colonies?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.50,0:20:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He sacrificed his life\Nwithout a second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.01,0:20:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.91,0:20:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My body!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.65,0:20:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.18,0:20:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can you hear me?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.55,0:20:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We must leave here at once!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.86,0:21:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.89,0:21:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That you, Trowa?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.10,0:21:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Without resolution we\Ncannot fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's accepted all orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they bluffed with\Nthe colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.64,0:21:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't fight any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.89,0:21:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry and move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.52,0:21:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't attack you in\Na position like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All Gundams are retreating\Nfrom their battle points!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.03,0:21:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't expect this to be\Nthe end, Gundams.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.50,0:21:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you, Lieutenant Noin!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.47,0:21:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel, I have a call in\Nfrom His Excellency.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.11,0:21:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.64,0:21:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.98,0:21:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He says for you to\Nbe more graceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.61,0:21:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,About everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.45,0:22:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,More graceful...\NLADY Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.09,0:23:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundams have been defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.19,0:23:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,With the colonies used as hostages,\Nthe warriors don't have a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.59,0:23:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They face a time of humiliation\Nwhen they are unable to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.86,0:23:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, no one can confirm\Nwhether Heero's dead or alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.60,0:23:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,About that time, Relena heads\Nto Moscow alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.70,0:23:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...having been informed that\NLady Une is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.67,0:23:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She aims her gun straight\Nat her father's killer, Lady Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.58,0:23:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.56,0:23:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Whereabouts of Happiness".
